==English==

===Noun===

# (''capitalized'') An adherent of the [[Episcopal]] Churches of America or Scotland.
#: ''I was raised an Episcopalian but no longer belong to a church.''

===Adjective===

# (''uncapitalized'') Of or relating to [[bishop]]s of whatever church.
#: ''A bishop is entitled to certain episcopalian privileges.''

